1.2 Identifying Common Combinations

1.2.1 Item Pairs

## # A tibble: 8 × 2
##   pairs                                       n
##   <chr>                                   <int>
## 1 scope.people & scope.person                56
## 2 target.race & target.religion              48
## 3 content.attack & scope.people              36
## 4 scope.people & target.race                 34
## 5 target.race & target.sex                   32
## 6 target.race & target.sexual_orientation    29
## 7 content.attack & scope.person              28
## 8 scope.people & target.religion             27

INTERPRETATION

  • people and person are mentioned a lot together as the scope of hate speech targets
  • attacking a person or people is maybe the best “common ground”
  • race and religion are mostly mentioned together as two potential target characteristics

1.2.2 Item Triples

## # A tibble: 8 × 2
##   triples                                                       n
##   <chr>                                                     <int>
## 1 scope.people & target.race & target.religion                 23
## 2 content.attack & target.race & target.religion               19
## 3 content.attack & scope.people & scope.person                 18
## 4 target.race & target.religion & target.sex                   18
## 5 target.race & target.religion & target.sexual_orientation    17
## 6 scope.people & scope.person & target.race                    16
## 7 scope.person & target.race & target.religion                 16
## 8 scope.people & scope.person & target.religion                14

INTERPRETATION

  • attack on people or person -> same as in pairs
  • people as scope, and race and religion (and sex / sexual orientation) as targets -> this is basically the most common definition, also in the literature
